---
import ServicePageShell from '../components/ServicePageShell.astro';

const sections = [
  {
    title: 'What website maintenance actually includes',
    paragraphs: [
      'Website maintenance is the ongoing work that keeps a business website reliable after launch. That includes security checks, backups, uptime monitoring, speed checks, broken form testing, content edits, and technical issue reviews. It also means watching for small problems before they become expensive ones.',
      'For most businesses, the value is continuity. Maintenance protects the website as a lead channel. It keeps the contact points working, keeps the site secure, and gives you someone responsible for technical health. It does not mean a full redesign every month, and it does not mean major new feature development. It means the website stays open, dependable, and commercially useful.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Why businesses in Kenya need ongoing website maintenance',
    paragraphs: [
      'Many Kenyan businesses get a website built once, then assume it will keep working forever. In reality, neglected websites get slower, forms stop sending leads, SSL certificates expire, hosting issues go unnoticed, and platform updates create layout or security problems. A site can remain online while still quietly losing enquiries.',
      'This is especially common when a business relied on a freelancer for a one-off build and no support process was put in place afterward. The site is technically live, but nobody is really managing it. Maintenance fixes that gap by making website reliability part of a regular service instead of an emergency reaction.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Website security, updates, and backup management',
    paragraphs: [
      'Security and backups are the highest-anxiety part of maintenance because the cost of failure is high. A hacked site, broken plugin, lost data, or expired SSL certificate can damage trust and interrupt lead flow immediately. Maintenance reduces that risk through regular checks, backup routines, admin cleanup, and platform-specific update discipline.',
      'For WordPress sites, that can include plugin, theme, and core update oversight, because every extra dependency adds more risk. For custom-built sites, the work may focus more on dependency reviews, hosting setup, SSL monitoring, and general technical health. Off-site backups, retention discipline, and restore readiness matter because a backup only helps if it can actually bring the site back quickly.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Performance monitoring and website support',
    paragraphs: [
      'Maintenance is not only about security. It also protects user experience and lead generation. Uptime monitoring helps catch downtime early. Core Web Vitals and performance reviews help keep the site fast. Broken links, failed pages, mobile issues, and form errors all affect trust, enquiries, and SEO if they are left alone.',
      'Support also matters. Businesses often need small but important updates: a service change, a price edit, a staff update, a new image, or a corrected phone number. A monthly support relationship gives the site an owner instead of leaving those edits delayed until something is badly out of date.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Website maintenance for WordPress sites vs custom-built sites',
    paragraphs: [
      'WordPress sites and custom-built sites do not age in the same way. WordPress often needs more update oversight because plugins and themes can conflict, create security exposure, or change the layout unexpectedly. The attack surface is usually higher because there are more moving parts.',
      'Custom-built websites are often cleaner to maintain because they rely on fewer external layers. That does not mean zero maintenance, but it usually means less plugin risk and fewer compatibility surprises. Tupate Studio can maintain both, but the lower-bloat custom approach is generally easier to protect over time. If you are comparing platforms, our guide to <a href="/articles/custom-website-vs-wordpress-kenya">custom-built websites vs WordPress in Kenya</a> explains the trade-offs clearly.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'How much website maintenance costs in Kenya',
    paragraphs: [
      'Website maintenance is different from basic hosting. Cheap hosting keeps files online. Maintenance keeps the website healthy, checked, and supported. Some businesses use a freelancer-on-call model, but that often means slow response times, unclear scope, and support only after something has already gone wrong.',
      'Tupate Studio positions website maintenance from <strong>Ksh 5,000/month</strong>. That gives businesses a clear retainer for technical continuity and support. The real comparison is not maintenance versus no maintenance. It is maintenance versus the cost of downtime, lost leads, emergency recovery, and technical neglect that slowly hurts SEO and conversion.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Tupate Studio website maintenance process',
    paragraphs: [
      'The process starts with a site review so we understand how the website is built, what access is available, and what the main technical risks are. From there, we can set a maintenance baseline through backups, monitoring, and routine checks. That makes future support more predictable and less reactive.',
      'After onboarding, the service becomes a monthly rhythm: checks, updates where relevant, support actions, and practical communication. If an urgent issue appears, there is already an existing support relationship in place. This also works for businesses whose sites were built by another developer. You do not need to start from scratch to put proper support around an existing site.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'How website maintenance supports SEO performance',
    paragraphs: [
      'Maintenance supports SEO by protecting the technical foundations Google depends on: speed, uptime, crawlability, mobile usability, and clean page behaviour. Broken forms, slow pages, dead links, and indexing issues all damage the long-term performance of a site.',
      'That is why maintenance and SEO are connected. Maintenance protects the website. SEO grows its visibility. If you want more active growth, our <a href="/articles/seo-services-kenya">SEO services in Kenya</a> and <a href="/articles/technical-seo-audit-kenya">technical SEO audit guide</a> show how those next layers work.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Website maintenance for businesses that need frequent content changes',
    paragraphs: [
      'Some businesses need more than technical checks. They also need frequent content support. That could mean price changes, new team members, updated services, event pages, gallery updates, or ongoing edits to keep the site aligned with what the business is actually doing.',
      'This is one reason a good site should also be built cleanly in the first place. Our <a href="/business-website-design-kenya">business website design service</a> creates a stronger base for maintenance because the structure is clearer from day one.',
    ],
  },
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Can Tupate Studio maintain a website built by someone else?',
    answer:
      'Yes. We can review the current setup, assess the risks, and take over ongoing support where the site is maintainable.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I need website maintenance if my site is small?',
    answer:
      'Yes. Even a small site can lose leads if forms fail, SSL expires, pages break, or performance declines over time.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What happens if my website goes down?',
    answer:
      'The maintenance process is designed to catch issues early, but when downtime happens, support can move faster because access and monitoring are already in place.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is website maintenance different from SEO?',
    answer:
      'Yes. Maintenance protects the website’s technical health, while SEO focuses on growing visibility and traffic.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How quickly can changes be made each month?',
    answer:
      'That depends on the scope of the updates, but routine support edits are handled much faster inside an ongoing maintenance arrangement than through one-off emergency requests.',
  },
];

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': ['Service', 'LocalBusiness'],
  name: 'Website Maintenance Services Kenya',
  provider: {
    '@type': 'LocalBusiness',
    name: 'Tupate Studio',
    url: 'https://tupate.studio',
  },
  serviceType: 'Website Maintenance',
  areaServed: {
    '@type': 'Country',
    name: 'Kenya',
  },
  offers: {
    '@type': 'Offer',
    priceCurrency: 'KES',
    price: '5000',
  },
};
---

<ServicePageShell
  title="Website Maintenance Services Kenya | Tupate Studio"
  description="Website maintenance services in Kenya for businesses that need security checks, backups, updates, uptime monitoring, and ongoing support. From Ksh 5,000/month."
  h1="Website Maintenance Services in Kenya for Businesses That Need Their Website to Stay Fast, Secure, and Working"
  intro="A website that is ignored becomes slower, less secure, and less reliable as a source of leads. Many Kenyan businesses only think about maintenance after a form stops working, an SSL expires, or a site gets hacked. Tupate Studio offers proactive website maintenance so your site stays live, usable, and ready to support customers and Google."
  priceLabel="From Ksh 5,000/month"
  serviceName="Website Maintenance"
  quoteSource="website-maintenance"
  quoteTitle="Need ongoing support for your website?"
  quoteSubtitle="Tell us about your current site and we will show you the right maintenance and support next step."
  heroPoints={[
    'Maintenance support from Ksh 5,000/month',
    'Backups, monitoring, form checks, and technical continuity',
    'Suitable for Tupate builds and existing third-party websites',
  ]}
  sections={sections}
  faqs={faqs}
  schema={schema}
/>
